  "description": "IRS Code 576 indicates a generated refund freeze. Learn what this freeze typically means, how it interacts with codes 570, 846, and 971, and what to verify before advising clients.",
  "content": "<nav class=\"text-sm text-slate-400\">\n    <ol class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\">\n      <li><a class=\"hover:text-white transition\" href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-600\">/</li>\n      <li><a class=\"hover:text-white transition\" href=\"/resources/transcript-types/\">Resources</a></li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-600\">/</li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-200\">IRS Code 576 Meaning</li>\n    </ol>\n   </nav>\n\n   <header class=\"mt-6\">\n    <div class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full tm-kbd px-4 py-2 text-xs text-slate-300\">\n      <span class=\"font-semibold text-white\">IRS Transcript Codes</span> <span class=\"text-slate-500\">•</span> <span>Built for 750,000+ U.S. Tax Professionals</span>\n    </div>\n    <h1 class=\"mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl\">IRS Code <span class=\"text-purple-300\">576</span> Meaning</h1>\n    <p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-base text-slate-300 tm-prose\">IRS Code 576 generally indicates <strong>a generated refund freeze</strong>. It means the IRS placed a hold on a refund amount pending review, adjustment, or notice activity.</p>\n    <div class=\"mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center\">\n      <button type=\"button\" data-open-sample class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-purple-400 transition\">View sample report</button>\n      <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400/30 transition\">Try the parser (requires credits)</a>\n    </div>\n   </header>\n\n   <section class=\"mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3\">\n    <article class=\"lg:col-span-2 tm-card rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8\">\n     <div class=\"tm-prose\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">What is IRS Code 576?</h2>\n      <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-300\"><strong>Plain-English definition:</strong> Code 576 reflects that <strong>a refund has been frozen after generation</strong>. The IRS typically applies this hold while verifying credits, reviewing adjustments, or issuing notices.</p>\n\n      <dl class=\"mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\">\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Common transcript type</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Account Transcript</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Often appears near</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Codes 570, 846</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Typical context</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Refund review or offset activity</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Client-friendly summary</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">\"Your refund is currently on hold\"</dd></div>\n      </dl>\n\n      <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">When does Code 576 appear?</h2>\n      <ul class=\"mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-slate-300\">\n        <li><strong>After refund generation:</strong> Applied once a refund amount is calculated.</li>\n        <li><strong>During review:</strong> May relate to credit verification or identity checks.</li>\n        <li><strong>Before final release:</strong> Often precedes either resolution (571) or issuance (846).</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">What should you verify?</h2>\n      <ol class=\"mt-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-slate-300 space-y-2\">\n        <li>Check for <strong>Code 571</strong> indicating freeze resolution.</li>\n        <li>Look for <strong>Code 846</strong> confirming refund issuance.</li>\n        <li>Review <strong>Code 971</strong> for notice explanation.</li>\n      </ol>\n\n      <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n      <h2 id=\"example\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">Example in a parsed report</h2>\n      <div class=\"code-block mt-5\">\n        <div class=\"code-label\">Refund freeze sequence</div>\n        <div class=\"space-y-3 text-sm\">\n          <div><span class=\"code-key\">Code 846</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Refund generated</span></div>\n          <div><span class=\"code-key\">Code 576</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Generated refund freeze</span></div>\n          <div><span class=\"code-key\">Code 571</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Freeze resolved</span></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n      <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">FAQ</h2>\n      <div class=\"mt-4 space-y-4\">\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">What does IRS Code 576 mean?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">It means the IRS placed a freeze on a generated refund.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">Does Code 576 stop payment?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Yes, it typically prevents the refund from being issued until resolved.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">Is Code 576 permanent?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">No, it usually remains until the IRS completes its review or verification.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">What other codes matter?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Review 570, 571, 846, and 971 for full context.</p></details>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </article>\n\n    <aside class=\"space-y-6\">\n      <div class=\"tm-card rounded-2xl p-6\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-base font-bold text-white\">Make this billable</h2>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Convert transcripts into a clean client-ready report.</p>\n        <button type=\"button\" data-open-sample class=\"mt-4 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-500 px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-purple-400 transition\">View sample report</button>\n        <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"mt-3 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400/30 transition\">Try the parser</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"tm-card rounded-2xl p-6\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-base font-bold text-white\">Related codes</h2>\n        <ul class=\"mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm\">\n          <li><a class=\"text-purple-300 hover:text-purple-200 transition\" href=\"/resources/transcript-codes/\">All codes</a></li>\n          <li><a class=\"text-purple-300 hover:text-purple-200 transition\" href=\"/resources/irs-code-570-meaning/\">IRS Code 570 Meaning</a></li>\n          <li><a class=\"text-purple-300 hover:text-purple-200 transition\" href=\"/resources/irs-code-571-meaning/\">IRS Code 571 Meaning</a></li>\n          <li><a class=\"text-purple-300 hover:text-purple-200 transition\" href=\"/resources/irs-code-846-meaning/\">IRS Code 846 Meaning</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"tm-card rounded-2xl p-6\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-base font-bold text-white\">Start here</h2>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">New to transcripts? Get the complete guide.</p>\n        <a class=\"mt-4 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400/30 transition\" href=\"/magnets/lead-magnet\">Get the complete guide</a>\n      </div>\n    </aside>\n   </section>",
